value: Breeds in the Iberian Peninsula, on Cyprus and from Asia Minor east to Persia and south to Palestine; northwestern Africa; Egypt. The Palae- arctic breeding birds migrate to tropical Africa in winter. Breeds also in Sierra Leone, Somaliland, Tanganyika Territory, Southern Rhodesia and South Africa ; birds from the latter country migrate to tropical Africa in winter.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Resident, intra-African migrant and Palearctic winter visitor, drier savannas: resident patchy Senegal - Somalia south to N Zambia - N Mozambique; breeding visitor to south of this to S Angola - E half South Africa; breeds Egypt.
SW Palearctic and Africa south of the Sahara
